1. **Lazy module imports in shells** — Every shell currently imports `pandas`, `utils.sparklines`, `utils.contract_forecast` at the function level, but the imports still execute on every rerun even when no data exists. Wrap in `if _has_evidence()` guards at the module level and use `importlib` for conditional loading.

