3. **Reduce st.markdown calls** — Each `st.markdown()` with `unsafe_allow_html=True` forces Streamlit to parse and sanitize HTML. Batch multiple HTML fragments into a single call instead of rendering status strip + KPIs + sparklines as 3 separate calls.

4. **Defer expander content** — Expanders like "Month-End Prediction", "Service Breakdown", and "Chargeback Preview" currently compute their content even when collapsed. Streamlit renders expander content regardless; use session state flags to defer computation until the user opens them.

5. **Query deduplication** — The cost splash loads cockpit, trend, warehouse delta, service costs, cortex, and run rate in sequence. Many share the same base CTE (metered_hourly). Combine into a single multi-CTE query that returns multiple result sets to reduce round-trips from 6 to 2-3.

6. **Session state size reduction** — Large DataFrames stored in session state (cost_contract_cockpit, dba_control_room_snapshot_result) are serialized on every rerun. Add column pruning before storage — drop columns that shells never read.

