7. **Prefer Dynamic Tables over live ACCOUNT_USAGE** — The DT migration script exists but the app still defaults to live queries. Switch the mart SQL builders to read from `V_OVERWATCH_*` views first, falling back to live only when DTs aren't deployed.

8. **Result size guards per section** — The existing `STANDARD_SQL_READ_LIMIT_ROWS = 5000` is a global cap. Sections like Warehouse Health only need 50 rows max for shell KPIs. Add per-section row limits to avoid transferring 5000 rows when 50 suffice.

9. **Partial cache invalidation** — Currently, changing the date range clears ALL loaded evidence. Only clear sections whose SQL includes date parameters. Metadata queries (warehouse lists, role inventory) don't change with dates and shouldn't be invalidated.

10. **Precomputed shell metrics** — Store pre-aggregated shell KPIs (total_credits, failure_count, etc.) as lightweight scalars in session state alongside the full DataFrame. The shell reads the scalar; only the full workspace reads the DataFrame.

